{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Can I say how delighted I am to be away"},{"time":5000,"text":"from the calm of Westminster and Whitehall? (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":10000,"text":"This is Kim, a nine-year-old Vietnam girl,"},{"time":14000,"text":"her back ruined by napalm,"},{"time":19000,"text":"and she awakened the conscience of the nation of America"},{"time":23000,"text":"to begin to end the Vietnam War."},{"time":26000,"text":"This is Birhan, who was the Ethiopian girl"},{"time":31000,"text":"who launched Live Aid in the 1980s,"},{"time":35000,"text":"15 minutes away from death when she was rescued,"},{"time":38000,"text":"and that picture of her being rescued is one that went round the world."},{"time":43000,"text":"This is Tiananmen Square."},{"time":46000,"text":"A man before a tank became a picture"},{"time":50000,"text":"that became a symbol for the whole world of resistance."},{"time":54000,"text":"This next is the Sudanese girl,"},{"time":58000,"text":"a few moments from death,"},{"time":61000,"text":"a vulture hovering in the background,"},{"time":64000,"text":"a picture that went round the world"},{"time":67000,"text":"and shocked people into action on poverty."},{"time":71000,"text":"This is Neda, the Iranian girl"},{"time":74000,"text":"who was shot while at a demonstration with her father in Iran"},{"time":78000,"text":"only a few weeks ago, and she is now the focus, rightly so,"},{"time":83000,"text":"of the YouTube generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86000,"text":"And what do all these pictures and events have in common?"},{"time":91000,"text":"What they have in common is what we see unlocks"},{"time":94000,"text":"what we cannot see."},{"time":97000,"text":"What we see unlocks the invisible ties"},{"time":102000,"text":"and bonds of sympathy that bring us together"},{"time":105000,"text":"to become a human community."},{"time":110000,"text":"What these pictures demonstrate is that"},{"time":113000,"text":"we do feel the pain of others,"},{"time":115000,"text":"however distantly."},{"time":117000,"text":"What I think these pictures demonstrate"},{"time":120000,"text":"is that we do believe in something bigger than ourselves."},{"time":124000,"text":"What these pictures demonstrate is"},{"time":127000,"text":"that there is a moral sense across all religions, across all faiths,"},{"time":132000,"text":"across all continents -- a moral sense that"},{"time":136000,"text":"not only do we share the pain of others,"},{"time":138000,"text":"and believe in something bigger than ourselves"},{"time":140000,"text":"but we have a duty to act when we see things"},{"time":142000,"text":"that are wrong that need righted,"},{"time":144000,"text":"see injuries that need to be corrected,"},{"time":146000,"text":"see problems that need to be rectified."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150000,"text":"There is a story about Olof Palme, the Swedish Prime Minister,"},{"time":154000,"text":"going to see Ronald Reagan in America in the 1980s."},{"time":157000,"text":"Before he arrived Ronald Reagan said --"},{"time":159000,"text":"and he was the Swedish Social Democratic Prime Minister --"},{"time":161000,"text":"\"Isn’t this man a communist?\""},{"time":164000,"text":"The reply was, \"No, Mr President, he’s an anti-communist.\""},{"time":168000,"text":"And Ronald Reagan said, \"I don’t care what kind of communist he is!\""},{"time":171000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":173000,"text":"Ronald Reagan asked Olof Palme,"},{"time":176000,"text":"the Social Democratic Prime Minister of Sweden,"},{"time":179000,"text":"\"Well, what do you believe in? Do you want to abolish the rich?\""},{"time":183000,"text":"He said, \"No, I want to abolish the poor.\""},{"time":186000,"text":"Our responsibility is to let everyone have the chance"},{"time":189000,"text":"to realize their potential to the full."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193000,"text":"I believe there is a moral sense and a global ethic"},{"time":197000,"text":"that commands attention from people of every religion"},{"time":200000,"text":"and every faith, and people of no faith."},{"time":204000,"text":"But I think what's new is that we now have the capacity"},{"time":208000,"text":"to communicate instantaneously across frontiers"},{"time":210000,"text":"right across the world."},{"time":213000,"text":"We now have the capacity to find common ground"},{"time":215000,"text":"with people who we will never meet,"},{"time":217000,"text":"but who we will meet through the Internet and through"},{"time":222000,"text":"all the modern means of communication;"},{"time":224000,"text":"that we now have the capacity to organize"},{"time":226000,"text":"and take collective action together"},{"time":229000,"text":"to deal with the problem or an injustice"},{"time":232000,"text":"that we want to deal with;"},{"time":234000,"text":"and I believe that this makes this a unique age in human history,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and it is the start of what I would call"},{"time":240000,"text":"the creation of a truly global society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"Go back 200 years when the slave trade was"},{"time":247000,"text":"under pressure from William Wilberforce and all the protesters."},{"time":252000,"text":"They protested across Britain."},{"time":254000,"text":"They won public opinion over a long period of time."},{"time":257000,"text":"But it took 24 years for the campaign to be successful."},{"time":261000,"text":"What could they have done with the pictures that they could have shown"},{"time":264000,"text":"if they were able to use the modern means of communication"},{"time":268000,"text":"to win people’s hearts and minds?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":270000,"text":"Or if you take Eglantyne Jebb,"},{"time":272000,"text":"the woman who created Save the Children 90 years ago."},{"time":275000,"text":"She was so appalled by what was happening in Austria"},{"time":279000,"text":"as a result of the First World War and what was happening to children"},{"time":283000,"text":"who were part of the defeated families of Austria,"},{"time":287000,"text":"that in Britain she wanted to take action,"},{"time":289000,"text":"but she had to go house to house,"},{"time":291000,"text":"leaflet to leaflet, to get people to attend a rally"},{"time":294000,"text":"in the Royal Albert Hall"},{"time":297000,"text":"that eventually gave birth to Save the Children,"},{"time":300000,"text":"an international organization that is now fully recognized"},{"time":303000,"text":"as one of the great institutions in our land and in the world."},{"time":307000,"text":"But what more could she have done"},{"time":309000,"text":"if she’d had the modern means of communications available to her"},{"time":312000,"text":"to create a sense that the injustice that people saw"},{"time":315000,"text":"had to be acted upon immediately?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"Now look at what’s happened in the last 10 years."},{"time":320000,"text":"In Philippines in 2001, President Estrada --"},{"time":323000,"text":"a million people texted each other about the corruption of that regime,"},{"time":328000,"text":"eventually brought it down and it was, of course, called the \"coup de text.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":334000,"text":"Then you have in Zimbabwe the first election under Robert Mugabe a year ago."},{"time":339000,"text":"Because people were able to take mobile phone photographs"},{"time":342000,"text":"of what was happening at the polling stations, it was impossible"},{"time":345000,"text":"for that Premier to fix that election in the way that he wanted to do."},{"time":349000,"text":"Or take Burma and the monks that were blogging out,"},{"time":353000,"text":"a country that nobody knew anything about that was happening, until these blogs"},{"time":357000,"text":"told the world that there was a repression,"},{"time":359000,"text":"meaning that lives were being lost"},{"time":361000,"text":"and people were being persecuted and Aung San Suu Kyi,"},{"time":364000,"text":"who is one of the great prisoners of conscience of the world,"},{"time":368000,"text":"had to be listened to."},{"time":370000,"text":"Then take Iran itself, and what people are doing today:"},{"time":374000,"text":"following what happened to Neda,"},{"time":377000,"text":"people who are preventing the security services of Iran finding those people"},{"time":383000,"text":"who are blogging out of Iran, any by everybody who is blogging,"},{"time":386000,"text":"changing their address to Tehran, Iran,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and making it difficult for the security services."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"Take, therefore, what modern technology is capable of:"},{"time":395000,"text":"the power of our moral sense allied to the power of communications"},{"time":402000,"text":"and our ability to organize internationally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405000,"text":"That, in my view, gives us the first opportunity as a community"},{"time":409000,"text":"to fundamentally change the world."},{"time":413000,"text":"Foreign policy can never be the same again. It cannot be run by elites;"},{"time":416000,"text":"it’s got to be run by listening to the public opinions of peoples who are blogging,"},{"time":421000,"text":"who are communicating with each other around the world."},{"time":424000,"text":"200 years ago the problem we had to solve was slavery."},{"time":428000,"text":"150 years ago I suppose the main problem in a country like ours"},{"time":432000,"text":"was how young people, children, had the right to education."},{"time":435000,"text":"100 years ago in most countries in Europe, the pressure was for the right to vote."},{"time":440000,"text":"50 years ago the pressure was for the right to social security and welfare."},{"time":445000,"text":"In the last 50-60 years we have seen fascism, anti-Semitism, racism, apartheid,"},{"time":451000,"text":"discrimination on the basis of sex and gender and sexuality;"},{"time":456000,"text":"all these have come under pressure"},{"time":458000,"text":"because of the campaigns that have been run by people to change the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462000,"text":"I was with Nelson Mandela a year ago, when he was in London."},{"time":466000,"text":"I was at a concert that he was attending to mark his birthday"},{"time":471000,"text":"and for the creation of new resources for his foundation."},{"time":476000,"text":"I was sitting next to Nelson Mandela -- I was very privileged to do so --"},{"time":480000,"text":"when Amy Winehouse came onto the stage. (Laughter)"},{"time":483000,"text":"And Nelson Mandela was quite surprised at the appearance of the singer"},{"time":487000,"text":"and I was explaining to him at the time who she was."},{"time":492000,"text":"Amy Winehouse said, \"Nelson Mandela and I have a lot in common."},{"time":498000,"text":"My husband too has spent a long time in prison.\""},{"time":503000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":506000,"text":"Nelson Mandela then went down to the stage"},{"time":510000,"text":"and he summarized the challenge for us all."},{"time":513000,"text":"He said in his lifetime he had climbed a great mountain, the mountain"},{"time":517000,"text":"of challenging and then defeating racial oppression and defeating apartheid."},{"time":521000,"text":"He said that there was a greater challenge ahead,"},{"time":524000,"text":"the challenge of poverty, of climate change -- global challenges"},{"time":528000,"text":"that needed global solutions"},{"time":530000,"text":"and needed the creation of a truly global society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534000,"text":"We are the first generation which is in a position to do this."},{"time":538000,"text":"Combine the power of a global ethic"},{"time":541000,"text":"with the power of our ability to communicate"},{"time":546000,"text":"and organize globally, with the challenges that we now face,"},{"time":550000,"text":"most of which are global in their nature."},{"time":553000,"text":"Climate change cannot be solved in one country,"},{"time":556000,"text":"but has got to be solved by the world working together."},{"time":559000,"text":"A financial crisis, just as we have seen, could not be solved"},{"time":561000,"text":"by America alone or Europe alone;"},{"time":563000,"text":"it needed the world to work together."},{"time":565000,"text":"Take the problems of security and terrorism and, equally,"},{"time":568000,"text":"the problem of human rights and development:"},{"time":570000,"text":"they cannot be solved by Africa alone;"},{"time":572000,"text":"they cannot be solved by America or Europe alone."},{"time":576000,"text":"We cannot solve these problems unless we work together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579000,"text":"So the great project of our generation, it seems to me,"},{"time":582000,"text":"is to build for the first time, out of a global ethic"},{"time":585000,"text":"and our global ability to communicate"},{"time":587000,"text":"and organize together, a truly global society,"},{"time":590000,"text":"built on that ethic but with institutions"},{"time":594000,"text":"that can serve that global society and make for a different future."},{"time":598000,"text":"We have now, and are the first generation with, the power to do this."},{"time":603000,"text":"Take climate change. Is it not absolutely scandalous"},{"time":605000,"text":"that we have a situation"},{"time":607000,"text":"where we know that there is a climate change problem,"},{"time":611000,"text":"where we know also that that will mean we have to give more resources"},{"time":614000,"text":"to the poorest countries to deal with that,"},{"time":616000,"text":"when we want to create a global carbon market,"},{"time":619000,"text":"but there is no global institution"},{"time":621000,"text":"that people have been able to agree upon"},{"time":623000,"text":"to deal with this problem?"},{"time":625000,"text":"One of the things that has got to come out of Copenhagen in the next few months"},{"time":628000,"text":"is an agreement that there will be"},{"time":630000,"text":"a global environmental institution"},{"time":632000,"text":"that is able to deal"},{"time":634000,"text":"with the problems of persuading the whole of the world"},{"time":637000,"text":"to move along a climate-change agenda."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"One of the reasons why an institution is not in itself enough"},{"time":651000,"text":"is that we have got to persuade people around the world"},{"time":653000,"text":"to change their behavior as well,"},{"time":655000,"text":"so you need that global ethic of fairness and responsibility"},{"time":658000,"text":"across the generations."},{"time":660000,"text":"Take the financial crisis."},{"time":662000,"text":"If people in poorer countries can be hit by a crisis that starts in New York"},{"time":668000,"text":"or starts in the sub-prime market of the United States of America."},{"time":672000,"text":"If people can find that that sub-prime product"},{"time":674000,"text":"has been transferred across nations"},{"time":676000,"text":"many, many times until it ends up in banks in Iceland"},{"time":678000,"text":"or the rest in Britain,"},{"time":680000,"text":"and people's ordinary savings are affected by it,"},{"time":683000,"text":"then you cannot rely on a system of national supervision."},{"time":686000,"text":"You need in the long run for stability, for economic growth,"},{"time":689000,"text":"for jobs, as well as for financial stability,"},{"time":692000,"text":"global economic institutions that make sure"},{"time":695000,"text":"that growth to be sustained has to be shared,"},{"time":697000,"text":"and are built on the principle"},{"time":699000,"text":"that the prosperity of this world is indivisible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702000,"text":"So another challenge for our generation is to create global institutions"},{"time":705000,"text":"that reflect our ideas of fairness and responsibility,"},{"time":709000,"text":"not the ideas that were the basis"},{"time":711000,"text":"of the last stage of financial development over these recent years."},{"time":716000,"text":"Then take development and take the partnership we need between our countries"},{"time":720000,"text":"and the rest of the world, the poorest part of the world."},{"time":725000,"text":"We do not have the basis of a proper partnership for the future,"},{"time":729000,"text":"and yet, out of people’s desire for a global ethic"},{"time":732000,"text":"and a global society that can be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735000,"text":"I have just been talking to the President of Sierra Leone."},{"time":738000,"text":"This is a country of six and a half million people,"},{"time":741000,"text":"but it has only 80 doctors; it has 200 nurses;"},{"time":745000,"text":"it has 120 midwives."},{"time":748000,"text":"You cannot begin to build a healthcare system for six million people"},{"time":752000,"text":"with such limited resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":755000,"text":"Or take the girl I met when I was in Tanzania,"},{"time":757000,"text":"a girl called Miriam."},{"time":759000,"text":"She was 11 years old; her parents had both died from AIDS,"},{"time":763000,"text":"her mother and then her father."},{"time":765000,"text":"She was an AIDS orphan being handed"},{"time":768000,"text":"across different extended families to be cared for."},{"time":771000,"text":"She herself was suffering from HIV;"},{"time":773000,"text":"she was suffering from tuberculosis."},{"time":775000,"text":"I met her in a field, she was ragged, she had no shoes."},{"time":779000,"text":"When you looked in her eyes, any girl at the age of eleven"},{"time":782000,"text":"is looking forward to the future,"},{"time":785000,"text":"but there was an unreachable sadness in that girl’s eyes"},{"time":789000,"text":"and if I could have translated that to the rest of the world for that moment,"},{"time":794000,"text":"I believe that all the work that it had done for the global HIV/AIDS fund"},{"time":798000,"text":"would be rewarded by people being prepared to make donations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801000,"text":"We must then build a proper relationship between the richest and"},{"time":805000,"text":"the poorest countries"},{"time":807000,"text":"based on our desire that they are able to fend for themselves"},{"time":810000,"text":"with the investment that is necessary in their agriculture,"},{"time":813000,"text":"so that Africa is not a net importer of food, but an exporter of food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817000,"text":"Take the problems of human rights and"},{"time":819000,"text":"the problems of security in so many countries around the world."},{"time":822000,"text":"Burma is in chains, Zimbabwe is a human tragedy,"},{"time":827000,"text":"in Sudan thousands of people have died unnecessarily"},{"time":830000,"text":"for wars that we could prevent."},{"time":833000,"text":"In the Rwanda Children's Museum,"},{"time":836000,"text":"there is a photograph of a 10-year-old boy"},{"time":840000,"text":"and the Children's Museum is commemorating the lives that were lost"},{"time":846000,"text":"in the Rwandan genocide where a million people died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850000,"text":"There is a photograph of a boy called David."},{"time":853000,"text":"Beside that photograph there is the information about his life."},{"time":857000,"text":"It said \"David, age 10.\""},{"time":860000,"text":"David: ambition to be a doctor."},{"time":863000,"text":"Favorite sport: football. What did he enjoy most?"},{"time":867000,"text":"Making people laugh."},{"time":870000,"text":"How did he die?"},{"time":873000,"text":"Tortured to death."},{"time":875000,"text":"Last words said to his mother who was also tortured to death:"},{"time":880000,"text":"\"Don't worry. The United Nations are coming.\""},{"time":884000,"text":"And we never did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"And that young boy believed our promises"},{"time":889000,"text":"that we would help people in difficulty in Rwanda,"},{"time":892000,"text":"and we never did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"So we have got to create in this world also"},{"time":896000,"text":"institutions for peacekeeping and humanitarian aid,"},{"time":899000,"text":"but also for reconstruction and security"},{"time":902000,"text":"for some of the conflict-ridden states of the world."},{"time":905000,"text":"So my argument today is basically this."},{"time":908000,"text":"We have the means by which we could create a truly global society."},{"time":911000,"text":"The institutions of this global society can be created by our endeavors."},{"time":917000,"text":"That global ethic can infuse the fairness and responsibility that is necessary"},{"time":921000,"text":"for these institutions to work,"},{"time":924000,"text":"but we should not lose the chance in this generation,"},{"time":927000,"text":"in this decade in particular, with President Obama in America,"},{"time":931000,"text":"with other people working with us around the world,"},{"time":934000,"text":"to create global institutions for the environment,"},{"time":936000,"text":"and for finance,"},{"time":938000,"text":"and for security and for development,"},{"time":940000,"text":"that make sense of our responsibility to other peoples,"},{"time":943000,"text":"our desire to bind the world together, and"},{"time":946000,"text":"our need to tackle problems that everybody knows exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":950000,"text":"It is said that in Ancient Rome that when Cicero spoke to his audiences,"},{"time":955000,"text":"people used to turn to each other and say about Cicero, \"Great speech.\""},{"time":961000,"text":"But it is said that in Ancient Greece"},{"time":963000,"text":"when Demosthenes spoke to his audiences,"},{"time":966000,"text":"people turned to each other and didn’t say \"Great speech.\""},{"time":969000,"text":"They said, \"Let's march.\""},{"time":971000,"text":"We should be marching towards a global society."},{"time":974000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}